  - Docs drift: dashboard README references env.example.txt and feature flags not used in code (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/README.md)
  - Hardcoded default service token in compose (sensitive default value) rather than requiring explicit config (zakops-agent-api/deployments/docker/
    docker-compose.yml)
  - Duplicate dashboard codebases with distinct env sets (monorepo dashboard vs standalone repo) (/home/zaks/zakops-agent-api/apps/
    dashboard/.env.local, /home/zaks/zakops-dashboard/.env.local)
  - Agent-api .env only includes two variables while config requires many (e.g., DATABASE_URL raises if missing) (zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-
    api/.env, zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/core/config.py)
  - Code expects envs not present in examples (e.g., LOCAL_EMBEDDER_URL, RAG_REST_TIMEOUT) (zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/core/config.py,
    zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/.env.example)

  #### What's Missing

  - A single, authoritative registry that marks required vs optional and provides defaults per service (inferred from scattered env + code usage
    across files above)
  - Consistent secret classification and rotation guidance; secrets appear in compose defaults and env files without central policy (zakops-agent-api/
    deployments/docker/docker-compose.yml, zakops-backend/.env)
  - Startup validation across all services (backend has DSN gate; agent-api only enforces DATABASE_URL, RAG does not) (zakops-backend/src/api/
    orchestration/main.py, zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/core/config.py, Zaks-llm/src/api/rag_rest_api.py)

  #### What Would Break

