  ### Area 3: Error Taxonomy — Findings

  #### What Exists

  - Backend defines ErrorCode enum and structured ErrorResponse with middleware handler for APIException/validation/generic errors (zakops-backend/
    src/api/shared/error_codes.py, zakops-backend/src/api/shared/responses.py, zakops-backend/src/api/shared/middleware/error_handler.py)
  - Backend returns structured health metrics and includes X-Trace-ID via tracing middleware (zakops-backend/src/api/shared/middleware/tracing.py,
    zakops-backend/src/api/shared/routers/health.py)
  - Dashboard normalizes three backend error shapes (FastAPI detail, auth error string, structured error object) (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/
    lib/error-normalizer.ts)
  - Dashboard ApiError class centralizes error handling and intercepts error payloads even on 200 responses (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/lib/
    api.ts)
  - Agent-api has a RequestValidationError handler returning {detail, errors} (zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/main.py)
  - Agent-api rate limit errors return {error, detail, retry_after} (zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/core/middleware/rate_limiter.py)
  - Agent-api SSE stream returns event: error with simple JSON payload (zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/api/v1/agent.py)
  - Dashboard middleware proxy returns JSON 502 with backend_unavailable and correlation ID (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/middleware.ts)
  - Surface 9 manifest codifies console.warn vs console.error expectations (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/types/design-system-manifest.ts)

  #### What's Ad-Hoc

  - Many backend endpoints raise FastAPI HTTPException with detail strings, bypassing structured ErrorResponse (zakops-backend/src/api/orchestration/
    main.py)
  - Agent-api mixes error shapes (validation handler, rate limit handler, HTTPException detail strings) without a single schema (zakops-agent-api/
    apps/agent-api/app/main.py, zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/core/middleware/rate_limiter.py, zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/api/v1/*.py)
  - Dashboard server routes sometimes log console.error on expected degradation while Surface 9 requires console.warn (zakops-agent-api/apps/
    dashboard/src/app/api/agent/activity/route.ts, zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/types/design-system-manifest.ts)
  - SSE error payloads are free-form and not aligned with HTTP error schema (zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/api/v1/agent.py)

  #### What's Missing

  - Unified, cross-service error schema for backend + agent-api + RAG (backend has one, others do not) (zakops-backend/src/api/shared/responses.py,
    zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/main.py, Zaks-llm/src/api/rag_rest_api.py)
  - Standardized machine-readable error codes in agent-api and RAG (backend uses ErrorCode; others do not) (zakops-backend/src/api/shared/
    error_codes.py, zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/api/v1/*.py)
  - Guaranteed correlation ID propagation into error payloads (backend only adds X-Trace-ID header; correlation in body only for ErrorResponse)
    (zakops-backend/src/api/shared/middleware/tracing.py, zakops-backend/src/api/shared/middleware/error_handler.py)

  #### What Would Break

  - Enforcing a strict error schema would break clients expecting detail or {error, message} shapes; dashboard normalizer currently supports multiple
    shapes (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/lib/error-normalizer.ts)
  - Standardizing SSE error events would require updates to agent-api streaming responses and dashboard client expectations (zakops-agent-api/apps/
    agent-api/app/api/v1/agent.py, zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/lib/api.ts)

  #### Recommended Manifest Contents

  - Error code registry with HTTP status mapping (backend ErrorCode can be source of truth) (zakops-backend/src/api/shared/error_codes.py)
  - Required error payload schema for HTTP + SSE (include trace_id/correlation_id) (zakops-backend/src/api/shared/responses.py, zakops-agent-api/apps/
    agent-api/app/api/v1/agent.py)
  - Logging rules (warn vs error) aligned with Surface 9 (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/types/design-system-manifest.ts)

