  ### Area 5: Performance Budget — Findings

  #### What Exists

  - Backend request timing/metrics middleware with slow-request threshold (SLOW_REQUEST_THRESHOLD_MS) and response header X-Response-Time (zakops-
    backend/src/api/shared/middleware/metrics.py)
  - /health/metrics endpoint returns request metrics and includes threshold config (zakops-backend/src/api/shared/routers/health.py)
  - Chat performance benchmark script with p50/p95 reporting (zakops-backend/src/core/chat_benchmark.py)
  - Chat timing instrumentation with phase breakdown (zakops-backend/src/core/chat_timing.py)
  - Agent-api Prometheus metrics with request/LLM histograms (zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/core/metrics.py)
  - Database performance supports indexes and pipeline summary view (zakops-backend/db/migrations/001_foundation_tables.sql, zakops-backend/db/
    migrations/023_stage_check_constraint.sql)
  - Dashboard data fetching uses Promise.allSettled at page level to avoid blocking on partial failures (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/app/
    dashboard/page.tsx, zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/app/hq/page.tsx)
  - React Query caching defaults reduce refetches (staleTime, retry) (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/components/layout/providers.tsx)

  #### What's Ad-Hoc

  - Performance baselines are mentioned but not recorded (no actual numbers) (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/audit/risk-assessment.md)
  - Dashboard Makefile performance target uses external script path (/home/zaks/scripts/chat_benchmark.py) and assumes backend port 8090 (port drift)
    (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/Makefile)
  - Dashboard pipeline API route uses Promise.all without fallback per request and fetches full deals list in server route, which can be heavy
    (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/app/api/pipeline/route.ts)
  - No explicit timeout in dashboard proxy middleware fetch (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/middleware.ts)

  #### What's Missing

  - No explicit performance budget or SLOs for key endpoints/pages (only a slow-request threshold) (zakops-backend/src/api/shared/middleware/
    metrics.py)
  - No Web Vitals or client-side performance instrumentation in dashboard (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/**)
  - No CI performance tests or bundle size budgets (zakops-agent-api/.github/workflows/ci.yml, zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/package.json)

  #### What Would Break

  - Enforcing tight response-time budgets could conflict with long LLM/RAG calls and existing timeouts (LLM benchmark uses 120s timeout) (zakops-
    backend/src/core/chat_benchmark.py)
  - Strict budgets on dashboard pipeline route could fail when it builds stage data from full deal list (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/app/api/
    pipeline/route.ts)

  #### Recommended Manifest Contents

  - Performance budgets per critical endpoint (p95/p99) and per page load (TTFB, data fetch latency) (zakops-backend/src/api/shared/middleware/
    metrics.py, zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/app/dashboard/page.tsx)
  - LLM/RAG latency budgets and timeout policy (zakops-backend/src/core/chat_benchmark.py, zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/services/rag_rest.py)
  - Bundle size tracking + Web Vitals instrumentation requirement for dashboard (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/package.json, zakops-agent-api/apps/
    dashboard/src/**)

  ### Cross-Cutting Observations

  - Surface 9 design system manifest already codifies error handling and data fetching conventions; Surfaces 10–14 must align rather than duplicate
    these rules (zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/types/design-system-manifest.ts)
  - Duplicate dashboard codebases and port drift create conflicting assumptions about backend location (8090 vs 8091) and env files (zakops-agent-api/
    apps/dashboard/Makefile, zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/.env.local, zakops-backend/docker-compose.yml, /home/zaks/zakops-dashboard/.env.local)
  - FSM tests are out of sync with canonical stage taxonomy, which undermines both error taxonomy and test coverage surfaces (zakops-backend/tests/
    unit/test_idempotency.py, zakops-backend/src/core/deals/workflow.py)
  - Dependency health and env registry are tightly coupled; URL/port drift appears in both compose and dashboard code (zakops-agent-api/deployments/
    docker/docker-compose.yml, zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/middleware.ts)
  - Surface ordering dependency (recommended): Surface 11 (Env Registry) -> Surface 10 (Dependency Health) -> Surface 12 (Error Taxonomy) -> Surface
    13 (Test Coverage Contract) -> Surface 14 (Performance Budget); env registry must define endpoints/URLs before health checks; error taxonomy
    should be standardized before tests/budgets assert on error shapes (zakops-agent-api/apps/agent-api/app/core/config.py, zakops-backend/src/api/
    shared/routers/health.py, zakops-backend/src/api/shared/error_codes.py, zakops-agent-api/apps/dashboard/src/types/design-system-manifest.ts)

